You are a hardware verification expert. Generate a list of named test scenarios for the following circuit.

Module: {{ module_name }}
Specification:
{{ spec | tojson(indent=2) }}

Each scenario must be independently testable and cover a distinct behaviour.
Include: normal cases, boundary cases, and corner cases with extreme valid values.

STRICT RULES — violating these will break the testbench:
- Only use valid logic values (0 or 1 for 1-bit signals; 0 to 2^N-1 for N-bit signals).
- Do NOT test "invalid" or "out-of-range" input values — digital logic has no such concept in simulation.
- Do NOT include scenarios that expect X or Z outputs from a purely combinational DUT.

Respond with ONLY a JSON array:
[
  {
    "name": "<short_scenario_name>",
    "description": "<what this scenario tests>",
    "inputs": {"<port>": <value_or_sequence>},
    "expected": {"<port>": <value_or_sequence>}
  }
]

Generate between 5 and 10 scenarios.
